        <!-- ============ EXPERIMENT 7 ============ -->
        <section class="exp" id="exp-7">
          <h2 class="exp-head">7 &middot; LTI system response</h2>
          <div class="exp-sub">y(t) = x(t) * h(t) &mdash; output as the convolution of input with impulse response</div>
          <div class="secbar">
            <button class="stab on" data-sec="aim">Aim</button>
            <button class="stab" data-sec="theory">Theory</button>
            <button class="stab" data-sec="proc">Procedure</button>
            <button class="stab" data-sec="sim">Simulation</button>
            <button class="stab" data-sec="quiz">Self-assessment</button>
            <button class="stab" data-sec="ref">References</button>
          </div>

          <div class="sec aim on"><div class="prose">To compute the output of a linear time-invariant system by convolving the input with the system impulse response h(t), and to relate the shape of h(t) &mdash; its decay, its width, its oscillation &mdash; to the filtering effect seen at the output.</div></div>

          <div class="sec theory"><div class="prose">
            <p>A linear time-invariant system is completely characterised by its <b>impulse response</b> h(t), the output produced by a unit impulse at the input. Because such a system is linear and time-invariant, any input is a superposition of shifted impulses and the output is the same superposition of shifted, scaled copies of h:</p>
            <div class="eqblock">y(t) = x(t) * h(t) = &int; x(s) h(t - s) ds<br>impulse in &rarr; h(t) out<br>stable if &int; |h(t)| dt is finite; causal if h(t)=0 for t&lt;0</div>
            <p>The impulse response acts as a filter. A slowly decaying exponential h(t) = e^(-at)u(t) is a leaky integrator that smooths and lags the input (a low-pass effect). A short narrow h barely alters the input. A damped sinusoid h rings, emphasising frequencies near its oscillation rate (a resonator). Here both x and h are sampled finely and the output is the discrete convolution sum, scaled by the time step to approximate the integral. Read the energy gain and the peak shift to quantify how the system reshapes its input.</p>
          </div></div>

          <div class="sec proc"><ol class="steps">
            <li>Open the <b>Simulation</b>. The cyan curve is the input x(t), the purple curve is the impulse response h(t), and the amber curve is the output y(t).</li>
            <li>Choose an <b>input</b> &mdash; a pulse, a step or a sinusoid.</li>
            <li>Choose an <b>impulse response</b> &mdash; a decaying exponential (integrator), a narrow pulse (near pass-through) or a damped sine (resonator).</li>
            <li>Adjust the <b>decay rate</b> and <b>width</b> of h and watch the output smooth, lag, or ring accordingly.</li>
            <li>Read the <b>energy gain</b>, the <b>peak delay</b> and whether the response is <b>stable</b>.</li>
          </ol></div>

          <div class="sec sim">
            <div class="layout">
              <div class="panel">
                <h3>Input, impulse response, output</h3>
                <canvas id="ltCv" width="660" height="380"></canvas>
                <div class="legend">
                  <span><i style="background:#67e8f9"></i> x(t) input</span>
                  <span><i style="background:#a78bfa"></i> h(t) response</span>
                  <span><i style="background:#fbbf24"></i> y(t) output</span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="panel">
                  <h3>System</h3>
                  <div class="row"><label>Input x(t)</label>
                    <select id="ltX"><option value="pulse">Rectangular pulse</option><option value="step">Step</option><option value="sin">Sinusoid burst</option><option value="impulse">Impulse</option></select>
                  </div>
                  <div class="row"><label>Response h(t)</label>
                    <select id="ltH"><option value="exp">Decaying exp (integrator)</option><option value="rect">Moving average</option><option value="damp">Damped sine (resonator)</option><option value="diff">Difference (high-pass)</option></select>
                  </div>
                  <div class="row"><label>Decay a</label><input type="range" id="ltA" min="0.3" max="6" step="0.1" value="1.5"><span class="val" id="ltAv">1.5</span></div>
                  <div class="row"><label>Width / freq</label><input type="range" id="ltW" min="0.3" max="4" step="0.1" value="1.2"><span class="val" id="ltWv">1.2</span></div>
                  <div class="btns"><button class="btn ghost" id="ltReset">Reset</button></div>
                  <div class="stats">
                    <div class="stat"><div class="k">Energy gain</div><div class="v sm" id="ltGain">--</div></div>
                    <div class="stat"><div class="k">Peak delay</div><div class="v sm" id="ltDelay">--</div></div>
                    <div class="stat"><div class="k">Sum h(t)dt</div><div class="v sm" id="ltDC">--</div></div>
                    <div class="stat"><div class="k">Stable?</div><div class="v sm" id="ltStable">--</div></div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="sec quiz"><div class="quiz" data-quiz="7"></div></div>

          <div class="sec ref"><ul class="refs">
            <li><b>Oppenheim, Willsky &amp; Nawab</b> &mdash; Signals and Systems, 2nd ed., Sec. 2.1-2.3. Prentice Hall.</li>
            <li><b>Lathi</b> &mdash; Linear Systems and Signals, 2nd ed., Ch. 2. Oxford.</li>
            <li><b>Virtual Labs (IIT)</b> &mdash; Signals and Systems: LTI Systems, vlab.co.in.</li>
          </ul></div>
        </section>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</main>

<script is:inline>
(function () {
  function $(id) { return document.getElementById(id); }
  var DPR = Math.max(1, Math.min(2, window.devicePixelRatio || 1));
  var REDRAW = {}; // populated by each experiment IIFE, consumed by the tab/sidebar switchers below

  function makeCtx(cv, logicalW, logicalH) {
    var cssW = cv.clientWidth || logicalW;
    var scale = cssW / logicalW;
    cv.width = Math.round(logicalW * DPR * scale);
    cv.height = Math.round(logicalH * DPR * scale);
    cv.style.height = (logicalH * scale) + 'px';
    var ctx = cv.getContext('2d');
    ctx.setTransform(DPR * scale, 0, 0, DPR * scale, 0, 0);
    return ctx;
  }

  var COL = {
    bg: '#08080b', grid: '#16161f', axis: '#2a2a35', text: '#9aa0aa',
    cyan: '#67e8f9', purple: '#a78bfa', amber: '#fbbf24', green: '#86efac',
    red: '#fca5a5', dim: '#3a4054'
  };

  // ---- shared plot helpers (logical coords) ----
  function clearBg(ctx, W, H) {
    ctx.fillStyle = COL.bg; ctx.fillRect(0, 0, W, H);
  }
  // draws axes for a panel mapping t in [tmin,tmax] -> x in [pad,W-pad], y in [yMin,yMax] -> [H-pad, pad]
  function makeMap(W, H, tmin, tmax, ymax, padL, padR, padT, padB) {
    padL = padL || 34; padR = padR || 12; padT = padT || 12; padB = padB || 22;
    var x0 = padL, x1 = W - padR, y0 = padT, y1 = H - padB;
    var sx = function (t) { return x0 + (t - tmin) / (tmax - tmin) * (x1 - x0); };
    var sy = function (v) { return (y0 + y1) / 2 - v / ymax * ((y1 - y0) / 2); };
    return { sx: sx, sy: sy, x0: x0, x1: x1, y0: y0, y1: y1, midY: (y0 + y1) / 2, tmin: tmin, tmax: tmax, ymax: ymax };
  }
  function drawGrid(ctx, m, W, H, label) {
    ctx.lineWidth = 1;
    // vertical grid every 1 unit of t
    var step = (m.tmax - m.tmin) <= 6 ? 1 : 2;
    ctx.strokeStyle = COL.grid;
    for (var t = Math.ceil(m.tmin); t <= m.tmax; t += step) {
      var x = m.sx(t);
      ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(x, m.y0); ctx.lineTo(x, m.y1); ctx.stroke();
    }
    // horizontal grid lines
    for (var k = -1; k <= 1; k++) {
      var y = m.midY - k * ((m.y1 - m.y0) / 2);
      ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(m.x0, y); ctx.lineTo(m.x1, y); ctx.stroke();
    }
    // axes
    ctx.strokeStyle = COL.axis; ctx.lineWidth = 1.2;
    ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(m.x0, m.midY); ctx.lineTo(m.x1, m.midY); ctx.stroke();
    var xz = m.sx(0);
    if (xz >= m.x0 && xz <= m.x1) { ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(xz, m.y0); ctx.lineTo(xz, m.y1); ctx.stroke(); }
    ctx.fillStyle = COL.text; ctx.font = '10px Geist Mono, monospace';
    ctx.textAlign = 'left';
    if (label) ctx.fillText(label, m.x0 + 4, m.y0 + 11);
    ctx.textAlign = 'center';
    ctx.fillText('t', m.x1 - 6, m.midY - 4);
  }
  function plotFn(ctx, m, fn, color, width, N) {
    N = N || 800; ctx.strokeStyle = color; ctx.lineWidth = width || 2;
    ctx.beginPath();
    var started = false;
    for (var i = 0; i <= N; i++) {
      var t = m.tmin + (m.tmax - m.tmin) * i / N;
      var v = fn(t);
      if (!isFinite(v)) { started = false; continue; }
      var px = m.sx(t), py = m.sy(v);
      if (py < m.y0 - 40) py = m.y0 - 40; if (py > m.y1 + 40) py = m.y1 + 40;
      if (!started) { ctx.moveTo(px, py); started = true; } else ctx.lineTo(px, py);
    }
    ctx.stroke();
  }
  function plotArr(ctx, m, arr, ts, color, width) {
    ctx.strokeStyle = color; ctx.lineWidth = width || 2;
    ctx.beginPath();
    for (var i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
      var px = m.sx(ts[i]), py = m.sy(arr[i]);
      if (i === 0) ctx.moveTo(px, py); else ctx.lineTo(px, py);
    }
    ctx.stroke();
  }

  // ===================================================================
  // EXPERIMENT 1 — SIGNAL GENERATOR & COMPLEX EXPONENTIAL
  // ===================================================================
  (function GEN() {
    var cv = $('g1Cv'); if (!cv) return;
    var ctx = makeCtx(cv, 660, 300);
    var phCv = $('g1Ph');
    var pctx = makeCtx(phCv, 660, 240);
    var LW = 660, LH = 300;
    var phase = 0, playing = true, last = 0;

    function read() {
      var A = parseFloat($('g1A').value);
      var f = parseFloat($('g1F').value);
      var p = parseFloat($('g1P').value) * Math.PI / 180;
      var sp = parseFloat($('g1Sp').value);
      $('g1Av').textContent = A.toFixed(2);
      $('g1Fv').textContent = f.toFixed(2) + ' Hz';
      $('g1Pv').textContent = Math.round(p * 180 / Math.PI) + '°';
      $('g1Spv').textContent = sp.toFixed(1) + 'x';
      return { A: A, f: f, p: p, sp: sp, w: $('g1Wave').value };
    }

    function frac(x) { return x - Math.floor(x); }
    // base signal (no animation phase) for stats; tt is total time arg
    function val(tt, c) {
      var A = c.A, f = c.f, ph = c.p;
      var arg = 2 * Math.PI * f * tt + ph;
      switch (c.w) {
        case 'sine': return A * Math.sin(arg);
        case 'square': return A * (Math.sin(arg) >= 0 ? 1 : -1);
        case 'triangle': {
          var u = frac(f * tt + ph / (2 * Math.PI));
          return A * (4 * Math.abs(u - 0.5) - 1) * -1 + 0; // -A..A triangle
        }
        case 'saw': {
          var s = frac(f * tt + ph / (2 * Math.PI));
          return A * (2 * s - 1);
        }
        case 'impulse': {
          // unit-area sample near t=0
          return (Math.abs(tt) < 0.04) ? A : 0;
        }
        case 'step': return tt >= 0 ? A : 0;
        case 'exp': return A * Math.exp((f - 2) * tt); // f acts as sigma offset
        case 'cexp': return A * Math.cos(arg); // real part
        default: return 0;
      }
    }
    function imagVal(tt, c) {
      var arg = 2 * Math.PI * c.f * tt + c.p;
      return c.A * Math.sin(arg);
    }

    function draw() {
      var c = read();
      var isCx = (c.w === 'cexp');
      $('g1ImLeg').style.display = isCx ? '' : 'none';
      phCv.style.display = isCx ? '' : 'none';
      $('g1PhTitle').style.display = isCx ? '' : 'none';

      clearBg(ctx, LW, LH);
      var ymax = (c.w === 'exp') ? c.A * 4 : c.A * 1.4 + 0.2;
      var m = makeMap(LW, LH, -4, 4, ymax, 34, 12, 12, 22);
      drawGrid(ctx, m, LW, LH, c.w + '  x(t)');

      if (c.w === 'impulse') {
        // draw a stem at t=0
        var x0 = m.sx(0), yTop = m.sy(c.A);
        ctx.strokeStyle = COL.cyan; ctx.lineWidth = 3;
        ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(x0, m.midY); ctx.lineTo(x0, yTop); ctx.stroke();
        ctx.fillStyle = COL.cyan; ctx.beginPath(); ctx.arc(x0, yTop, 4, 0, 2 * Math.PI); ctx.fill();
        ctx.fillStyle = COL.text; ctx.font = '10px Geist Mono'; ctx.textAlign = 'center';
        ctx.fillText('δ(t)  area=' + c.A.toFixed(2), x0, yTop - 8);
      } else {
        plotFn(ctx, m, function (t) { return val(t + phase, c); }, COL.cyan, 2.2, 900);
        if (isCx) plotFn(ctx, m, function (t) { return imagVal(t + phase, c); }, COL.purple, 1.8, 900);
      }

      // phasor
      if (isCx) {
        clearBg(pctx, 660, 240);
        var cx = 660 / 2, cy = 240 / 2, R = 80;
        pctx.strokeStyle = COL.axis; pctx.lineWidth = 1;
        pctx.beginPath(); pctx.moveTo(cx - 110, cy); pctx.lineTo(cx + 110, cy); pctx.stroke();
        pctx.beginPath(); pctx.moveTo(cx, cy - 100); pctx.lineTo(cx, cy + 100); pctx.stroke();
        pctx.strokeStyle = COL.grid;
        pctx.beginPath(); pctx.arc(cx, cy, R * c.A, 0, 2 * Math.PI); pctx.stroke();
        var ang = 2 * Math.PI * c.f * phase + c.p;
        var ex = cx + R * c.A * Math.cos(ang), ey = cy - R * c.A * Math.sin(ang);
        // projections
        pctx.strokeStyle = COL.cyan; pctx.lineWidth = 1; pctx.setLineDash([3, 3]);
        pctx.beginPath(); pctx.moveTo(ex, ey); pctx.lineTo(ex, cy); pctx.stroke();
        pctx.strokeStyle = COL.purple;
        pctx.beginPath(); pctx.moveTo(ex, ey); pctx.lineTo(cx, ey); pctx.stroke();
        pctx.setLineDash([]);
        pctx.strokeStyle = COL.amber; pctx.lineWidth = 2.4;
        pctx.beginPath(); pctx.moveTo(cx, cy); pctx.lineTo(ex, ey); pctx.stroke();
        pctx.fillStyle = COL.amber; pctx.beginPath(); pctx.arc(ex, ey, 4, 0, 2 * Math.PI); pctx.fill();
        pctx.fillStyle = COL.cyan; pctx.font = '10px Geist Mono'; pctx.textAlign = 'center';
        pctx.fillText('Re', ex, cy + 14);
        pctx.fillStyle = COL.purple; pctx.textAlign = 'right';
        pctx.fillText('Im', cx - 6, ey + 3);
      }

      // stats
      var peak = 0, sumsq = 0, ns = 600;
      for (var i = 0; i < ns; i++) {
        var t = -4 + 8 * i / ns;
        var v = val(t, c);
        if (Math.abs(v) > peak) peak = Math.abs(v);
        sumsq += v * v;
      }
      var rms = Math.sqrt(sumsq / ns);
      $('g1Peak').textContent = peak.toFixed(3);
      $('g1Rms').textContent = rms.toFixed(3);
      if (c.w === 'impulse' || c.w === 'step' || c.w === 'exp') $('g1Per').textContent = 'n/a';
      else $('g1Per').textContent = (1 / c.f).toFixed(3) + ' s';
      $('g1Om').textContent = (2 * Math.PI * c.f).toFixed(2);
    }

    ['g1Wave', 'g1A', 'g1F', 'g1P', 'g1Sp'].forEach(function (id) {
      $(id).addEventListener('input', draw); $(id).addEventListener('change', draw);
    });
    $('g1Play').addEventListener('click', function () { playing = !playing; this.textContent = playing ? 'Pause' : 'Play'; });
    $('g1Reset').addEventListener('click', function () {
      $('g1A').value = 1; $('g1F').value = 1; $('g1P').value = 0; $('g1Sp').value = 1.5; $('g1Wave').value = 'sine';
      phase = 0; draw();
    });

    REDRAW['1'] = function () { ctx = makeCtx(cv, 660, 300); pctx = makeCtx(phCv, 660, 240); draw(); };

    function loop(ts) {
      if (!last) last = ts; var dt = (ts - last) / 1000; last = ts;
      if (playing) { var c = read(); phase += dt * c.sp * 0.5; }
      if ($('exp-1').classList.contains('on')) draw();
      requestAnimationFrame(loop);
    }
    draw(); requestAnimationFrame(loop);
  })();

  // ===================================================================
  // EXPERIMENT 2 — EVEN / ODD DECOMPOSITION
  // ===================================================================
  (function EVENODD() {
    var cv = $('eoCv'); if (!cv) return;
    var ctx = makeCtx(cv, 660, 460);
    var LW = 660, LH = 460;

    function read() {
      var sh = parseFloat($('eoShift').value);
      var w = parseFloat($('eoW').value);
      var asym = parseFloat($('eoAsym').value);
      $('eoShiftv').textContent = sh.toFixed(1);
      $('eoWv').textContent = w.toFixed(1);
      $('eoAsymv').textContent = asym.toFixed(2);
      return { sh: sh, w: w, asym: asym, kind: $('eoWave').value };
    }
    function base(t, c) {
      switch (c.kind) {
        case 'gauss': return Math.exp(-Math.pow((t - c.sh) / c.w, 2)) * (1 + c.asym * (t - c.sh) * 0.4);
        case 'exp': { var tt = t - c.sh; return tt >= 0 ? Math.exp(-tt / c.w) : 0; }
        case 'ramp': { var u = t - c.sh; return (u >= 0 && u <= 2 * c.w) ? u / (2 * c.w) : 0; }
        case 'cos': return Math.cos(2 * Math.PI * (t) / (4 / c.w));
        case 'sin': return Math.sin(2 * Math.PI * (t) / (4 / c.w));
        default: return 0;
      }
    }
    function draw() {
      var c = read();
      clearBg(ctx, LW, LH);
      var third = LH / 3;
      var tmin = -4, tmax = 4, ymax = 1.6;
      // precompute energies
      var ns = 1000, Ee = 0, Eo = 0, err = 0, dt = (tmax - tmin) / ns, sym = 0, asw = 0;
      function xe(t) { return (base(t, c) + base(-t, c)) / 2; }
      function xo(t) { return (base(t, c) - base(-t, c)) / 2; }
      for (var i = 0; i < ns; i++) {
        var t = tmin + i * dt;
        var e = xe(t), o = xo(t), x = base(t, c);
        Ee += e * e * dt; Eo += o * o * dt;
        err += Math.abs((e + o) - x);
        sym += Math.abs(e); asw += Math.abs(o);
      }
      // panel maps
      var m1 = makeMap(LW, third, tmin, tmax, ymax, 34, 12, 8, 14);
      drawGrid(ctx, m1, LW, third, 'x(t)');
      plotFn(ctx, m1, function (t) { return base(t, c); }, COL.cyan, 2.2);

      ctx.save(); ctx.translate(0, third);
      var m2 = makeMap(LW, third, tmin, tmax, ymax, 34, 12, 8, 14);
      drawGrid(ctx, m2, LW, third, 'xe(t) even = (x(t)+x(-t))/2');
      plotFn(ctx, m2, xe, COL.green, 2.2);
      ctx.restore();

      ctx.save(); ctx.translate(0, 2 * third);
      var m3 = makeMap(LW, third, tmin, tmax, ymax, 34, 12, 8, 14);
      drawGrid(ctx, m3, LW, third, 'xo(t) odd = (x(t)-x(-t))/2');
      plotFn(ctx, m3, xo, COL.amber, 2.2);
      // overlay reconstruction on top panel (dashed)
      ctx.restore();
      ctx.save();
      ctx.setLineDash([4, 3]);
      plotFn(ctx, m1, function (t) { return xe(t) + xo(t); }, COL.red, 1.3);
      ctx.setLineDash([]);
      ctx.restore();

      $('eoEe').textContent = Ee.toFixed(3);
      $('eoEo').textContent = Eo.toFixed(3);
      $('eoErr').textContent = (err / ns).toExponential(1);
      var domE = sym / (sym + asw + 1e-9);
      $('eoSym').textContent = domE > 0.85 ? 'mostly even' : domE < 0.15 ? 'mostly odd' : 'mixed';
    }
    ['eoWave', 'eoShift', 'eoW', 'eoAsym'].forEach(function (id) {
      $(id).addEventListener('input', draw); $(id).addEventListener('change', draw);
    });
    REDRAW['2'] = function () { ctx = makeCtx(cv, 660, 460); draw(); };
    draw();
  })();

  // ===================================================================
  // EXPERIMENT 3 — TIME TRANSFORMATIONS
  // ===================================================================
  (function TIMET() {
    var cv = $('ttCv'); if (!cv) return;
    var ctx = makeCtx(cv, 660, 320);
    var LW = 660, LH = 320;

    function read() {
      var sh = parseFloat($('ttShift').value);
      var a = parseFloat($('ttScale').value);
      var rev = $('ttRev').value === '1';
      $('ttShiftv').textContent = sh.toFixed(1);
      $('ttScalev').textContent = a.toFixed(2);
      return { sh: sh, a: a, rev: rev, kind: $('ttWave').value };
    }
    function base(t) {
      var k = $('ttWave').value;
      switch (k) {
        case 'pulse': return (t >= -0.5 && t <= 1.5) ? (t < 0.5 ? 1 : 0.5) : 0;
        case 'tri': return (Math.abs(t) <= 1) ? 1 - Math.abs(t) : 0;
        case 'gauss': return Math.exp(-t * t * 1.5);
        case 'sin': return (Math.abs(t) <= 2) ? Math.sin(Math.PI * t) * Math.cos(t * 0.4) : 0;
        default: return 0;
      }
    }
    function draw() {
      var c = read();
      var aeff = c.rev ? -c.a : c.a;
      clearBg(ctx, LW, LH);
      var m = makeMap(LW, LH, -5, 5, 1.4, 34, 12, 12, 22);
      var lbl = 'y(t) = x(' + aeff.toFixed(2) + ' t' + (c.sh !== 0 ? (c.sh > 0 ? ' - ' + c.sh.toFixed(1) : ' + ' + Math.abs(c.sh).toFixed(1)) : '') + ')';
      drawGrid(ctx, m, LW, LH, lbl);
      // original faint
      plotFn(ctx, m, base, COL.dim, 1.6);
      // transformed: y(t) = x(aeff*t - sh)
      var pkAt = null, pkVal = -1;
      plotFn(ctx, m, function (t) {
        var arg = aeff * t - c.sh;
        var v = base(arg);
        if (v > pkVal) { pkVal = v; pkAt = t; }
        return v;
      }, COL.cyan, 2.4);

      // mapping label
      var mapTxt = 'y(t) = x(' + aeff.toFixed(2) + ' t' + (c.sh !== 0 ? (c.sh > 0 ? ' - ' + c.sh.toFixed(1) : ' + ' + Math.abs(c.sh).toFixed(1)) : '') + ')';
      $('ttMap').textContent = mapTxt;
      $('ttAeff').textContent = aeff.toFixed(2);
      $('ttDel').textContent = (c.sh / (c.a || 1)).toFixed(2);
      var acts = [];
      if (c.rev) acts.push('reverse');
      if (Math.abs(c.a - 1) > 0.01) acts.push(c.a > 1 ? 'compress' : 'stretch');
      if (Math.abs(c.sh) > 0.01) acts.push(c.sh > 0 ? 'delay' : 'advance');
      $('ttAct').textContent = acts.length ? acts.join(' + ') : 'none';
      $('ttPk').textContent = pkAt === null ? '--' : pkAt.toFixed(2);
    }
    ['ttWave', 'ttShift', 'ttScale', 'ttRev'].forEach(function (id) {
      $(id).addEventListener('input', draw); $(id).addEventListener('change', draw);
    });
    $('ttReset').addEventListener('click', function () {
      $('ttShift').value = 0; $('ttScale').value = 1; $('ttRev').value = '0'; draw();
    });
    REDRAW['3'] = function () { ctx = makeCtx(cv, 660, 320); draw(); };
    draw();
  })();

  // ===================================================================
  // EXPERIMENT 4 — CONVOLUTION (flip and slide)
  // ===================================================================
  (function CONV() {
    var cv = $('cvCv'); if (!cv) return;
    var ctx = makeCtx(cv, 660, 300);
    var outCv = $('cvOut');
    var octx = makeCtx(outCv, 660, 200);
    var LW = 660, LH = 300, OW = 660, OH = 200;
    var tau = -5, playing = false, last = 0;
    var dt = 0.02; // integration step
    var tmin = -5, tmax = 5;
    var outTaus = [], outVals = [], peakY = 0;

    function sig(kind, s) {
      switch (kind) {
        case 'rect': return (s >= 0 && s <= 2) ? 1 : 0;
        case 'tri': return (s >= 0 && s <= 2) ? (1 - Math.abs(s - 1)) : 0;
        case 'exp': return s >= 0 ? Math.exp(-s) : 0;
        case 'impulse': return (Math.abs(s) < dt) ? (1 / dt) : 0;
        default: return 0;
      }
    }
    function read() {
      tau = parseFloat($('cvTau').value);
      $('cvTauv').textContent = tau.toFixed(1);
      $('cvSpv').textContent = parseFloat($('cvSp').value).toFixed(1) + 'x';
      return { x: $('cvX').value, h: $('cvH').value };
    }
    // convolution value at shift t: integral x(s) h(t - s) ds
    function convAt(c, t) {
      var sum = 0;
      for (var s = tmin; s <= tmax; s += dt) {
        sum += sig(c.x, s) * sig(c.h, t - s) * dt;
      }
      return sum;
    }
    function rebuildOutput(c) {
      outTaus = []; outVals = []; peakY = 0;
      for (var t = tmin; t <= tmax; t += 0.05) {
        var v = convAt(c, t);
        outTaus.push(t); outVals.push(v);
        if (v > peakY) peakY = v;
      }
    }
    function draw() {
      var c = read();
      clearBg(ctx, LW, LH);
      var m = makeMap(LW, LH, tmin, tmax, 1.6, 34, 12, 12, 22);
      drawGrid(ctx, m, LW, LH, 'x(s) and flipped h(' + tau.toFixed(1) + '-s)');
      // overlap shading (product)
      ctx.fillStyle = 'rgba(134,239,172,0.22)';
      ctx.beginPath();
      var startShade = false;
      for (var s = tmin; s <= tmax; s += dt) {
        var prod = sig(c.x, s) * sig(c.h, tau - s);
        var pv = Math.min(prod, 1.55);
        var px = m.sx(s), py = m.sy(pv);
        if (!startShade) { ctx.moveTo(px, m.midY); startShade = true; }
        ctx.lineTo(px, py);
      }
      ctx.lineTo(m.sx(tmax), m.midY); ctx.closePath(); ctx.fill();
      // x(s)
      plotFn(ctx, m, function (s) { return Math.min(sig(c.x, s), 1.55); }, COL.cyan, 2.2, 1000);
      // flipped + shifted h
      plotFn(ctx, m, function (s) { return Math.min(sig(c.h, tau - s), 1.55); }, COL.purple, 2.2, 1000);
      // marker line at tau
      ctx.strokeStyle = COL.amber; ctx.lineWidth = 1; ctx.setLineDash([3, 3]);
      var xt = m.sx(tau); ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(xt, m.y0); ctx.lineTo(xt, m.y1); ctx.stroke();
      ctx.setLineDash([]);

      // output panel
      clearBg(octx, OW, OH);
      var ym = peakY > 0 ? peakY * 1.25 : 1;
      var mo = makeMap(OW, OH, tmin, tmax, ym, 34, 12, 12, 22);
      drawGrid(octx, mo, OW, OH, 'y(τ) = ∫ x(s) h(τ-s) ds');
      // draw output up to current tau (accumulating)
      octx.strokeStyle = COL.amber; octx.lineWidth = 2.4; octx.beginPath();
      var drawn = false;
      for (var i = 0; i < outTaus.length; i++) {
        if (outTaus[i] > tau + 1e-6) break;
        var px = mo.sx(outTaus[i]), py = mo.sy(outVals[i]);
        if (!drawn) { octx.moveTo(px, py); drawn = true; } else octx.lineTo(px, py);
      }
      octx.stroke();
      // current overlap area = current y
      var areaNow = convAt(c, tau);
      // dot at current point
      octx.fillStyle = COL.green;
